[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/1319 done id=gsm8k_test_7 prediction='First, calculate the total time Carla would take to download the 200 GB file at her normal rate of 2 GB per minute.  \nTotal time without interruptions = Total size ÷ Rate = 200 GB ÷ 2 GB/minute = 100 minutes.  \n\nNext, determine how far she has downloaded before the forced restart.  \n40% of 200 GB = 0.4 × 200 = 80 GB.  \n\nTime to download the first 80 GB at 2 GB/minute:  \n80 GB ÷ 2 GB/minute = 40 minutes.  \n\nAt this point, she has been downloading for 40 minutes.  \nThen, Windows restarts her download for 20 minutes, but no data is downloaded during this time.  \n\nAfter the restart, she has to re-download the entire 200 GB from scratch.  \nTime to re-download 200 GB at 2 GB/minute = 200 ÷ 2 = 100 minutes.  \n\nTotal time = time before restart (40 minutes) + restart time (20 minutes) + re-download time (100 minutes)  \n= 40 + 20 + 100 = 160 minutes.  \n\nTo find the total amount of data downloaded, note that the only data downloaded' gold='160' correct=False
